See more of what the documentation could do for a development project at http://pythonhosted.org/twx.botapi/

The Yummly Ruby SDK by Theo Mills allows unofficial interaction with the API, providing references to integrate food recommendations into applications. Resources include gem installation and Key & ID configuration. JSON responses display recipe objects.

The Yummly Node.js SDK by Yummly allows interaction with the API, providing guides to implement food recommendation features into an application. Resources explain how to register for an account, install Yummly module, require recipes, and call recipe functions.

The Zendesk C# SDK by Elizabeth Schneider allows interaction with the API features of support for businesses, mainly in the form of tickets. On GitHub, developers can find ways to create a ticket, get tickets, and upload an attachment to a ticket. Connect to developer for upcoming API changes.

The Zendesk R SDK by Zendesk allows interaction with the Version 2 of the API. It contains installation with Gems and with Bundler. It also provides configuration. The usage section explains how to work with pagination, callbacks, side-loading, and tickets. For more info, contact developer steven.davidovitz@gmail.com

The Sinch Video JavaScript SDK by Sinch assists in the implementation of the video communication features of the API. Developers can download the kit from the official website and then add it to a project. Once users have created an application, they will be able to call and send a first message.

The MediaFire C++ SDK aims to simplify interaction with the MediaFire API. Contains resources to manage the user session, manage uploads to MediaFire, and communicate with the API. Boost, an open source tool with peer reviewed CC++ source libraries, is required to build with this project.

The MediaFire Python SDK interacts with the MediaFire Core API, which offers billing, contact, and notification features just to mention a sample. Available instructions for usage and download. Requires Python 2.7 or 3.4, requests, and responses for testing.

The MediaFire PHP SDK by MediaFire provides resources to interact with the API. Requirements include PHP5 or higher, JSON extension, and open SSL, while optional tools involve limxml PHP extension enabled and cURL extension enabled. To use, developers can register and create a new application and next, obtain an AppID and an Api Key.

The MediaFire Objective-C SDK aims to increase the amount of interactions with MediaFire users from all over the world and add API features to iOS and Mac OSX applications. Contains API methods and core modules. For more information about integration opportunities, visit http://www.mediafire.com/developers/

The MediaFire JavaScript SDK by MediaFire features API, installation, and connector framework along with instructions to get started, use the login button, and upload files. MediaFire offers file sharing, cloud, and storage services and 3 APIs to integrate such functions into websites and mobile apps.

The MediaFire Java SDK by MediaFire offers flexibility and simplicity to add API features to Android or Java applications. It contains guides to get started and examples to use the SDK. It also provides custom API calls and uploader components. From the repository, developers can download the Java SDK.

The Mendeley iOS SDK by Mendeley aims to simplify the integration of the API in Apple devices. It offers methods and classes for Mac OSX and iOS applications. In addition, it provides instructions to install with CocoaPods and with repository cloning. Because this is an early version, developers are invited to contribute. Authored by Peter Schmidt.

The Mendeley JavaScript SDK by Mendeley aims to facilitate the interaction with the API. Contains bower installation and cloning installation. It is available as an AMD module or a standalone library. To work with the SDK, developers can register a client, begin with OAuth2, and authorize code flow. Examples available in the usage section. Also accessible, interactive API console at https://api.mendeley.com/apidocs Created by Paul Willoughby

TripAdvisor Facebook Android SDK by TripAdvisor. Allows to integrate travel functionalities into Facebook applications with the aim to engage users socially. Includes documentation to login, sharing, AppLinks, and Graph API. Authored by Kedar Sarmalkar. For more information, visit https://developers.facebook.com/docs/android

The official TelAPI JavaScript SDK interacts with the API to build applications in the cloud that feature SMS and voice services. Guides explain how to create a TelAPI application, generate credentials, and implement the client side code. Based in WebRTC, this resource could help developers to shorten the waiting time between users of mobile applications.

NationBuilder promotes leadership of citizens through fundraisers, social campaigns, and the creation of social communities driven by change. The NationBuilder PHP SDK interacts with the OAuth 2.0 protocol to build websites and applications with communications settings, finances tools, and data management features included in the API. Authors Charron Pierrick and Berejeb Anis can be reached at pierrick@webstart.fr and anis.berejeb@gmail.com respectively.

The Polljoy JavaScript SDK by Polljoy allows developers to integrate Polljoy's functions into their JavaScript applications. Polljoy is an in-game survey and engagement service designed to add polls to games and solicit user feedback. Polls can be personalized with custom graphics, sounds, and virtual currencies in order to fit the developer's game.

The Polljoy Android SDK by Polljoy allows developers to integrate Polljoy's functions into their Android apps written in Java. Polljoy is an in-game survey and engagement service designed to add polls to games and solicit user feedback. Polls can be personalized with custom graphics, sounds, and virtual currencies in order to fit the developer's game.

The Polljoy iOS SDK by Polljoy allows developers to integrate Polljoy's functions into their iOS apps written in Objective-C. Polljoy is an in-game survey and engagement service designed to add polls to games and solicit user feedback. Polls can be personalized with custom graphics, sounds, and virtual currencies in order to fit the developer's game.

The Polljoy Unity SDK by Polljoy allows developers to integrate Polljoy's functions into their Unity apps. Polljoy is an in-game survey and engagement service designed to add polls to games and solicit user feedback. Polls can be personalized with custom graphics, sounds, and virtual currencies in order to fit the developer's game.

The official 7digital Android SDK affords to integrate music charts, metadata, streams, and purchases into an Android application. 7digital is a service that offers over 30 million music tracks with curated recommendations. What author Ling Khor created to demonstrate how his project works, was the 7digital Android Buy Button. This sample allows users to buy a track without leaving the app. This is the project: https://github.com/7digital/7digital-android-buy-button-demo
Full API documentation available at: http://7digital.github.io/7digital-Android-SDK/apidocs/

The Oodle Ruby SDK by Albert Vernon allows developers to add classified listings into websites. Filters include categories, regions, and keywords. Includes installation, example, and dependencies. This project needs an Api Key to start implementation.

The Livefyre Android SDK authored by Gibron Kury, offers guides to integrate in Android Studio and Eclipse. Livefyre engage consumers through social reviews posted in social media and integrated in web platforms. With this in mind, the author created a sample app to study how to include reviews into a web app. This is the reference implementation: https://github.com/Livefyre/StreamHub-Android-Reviews-App

Use the official Livefyre iOS SDK to integrate as a CocoaPod or Xcode subproject. API capabilities allow customers to experience real time marketing campaigns with social media in galleries, media walls, maps, and sidenotes applications. Requirements include iOS 6.0 or higher. By Eugene Scherba.

With the Ooyala iOS SDK by Ooyala, developers can integrate diverse API functionalities into Apple apps. Such functionalities include playback, thumbnails, related media, live, ads, analytics, and closed captions. Download the SDK from this link: http://support.ooyala.com/developers/documentation/concepts/mobile_sdk_ios_download.html

The Ooyala Android SDK by Ooyala aims to facilitate application development with integrated video embedded on the app. Three options are available for Android developers: Mobility SDK for Android, SDK for Google IMA Android, and SDK for FreeWheen Android. See the developers guide for additional information at http://support.ooyala.com/developers/documentation/concepts/chapter_sdk_android.html

The Brewery DB iOS SDK by Brewery DB is still a work in progress and invites developers to contribute. The aim of this project is to interact with the API services of brewery search to create Apple applications with regional breweries, beer style guide, and brewers guilds.

The official Brewery DB Java SDK provides usage and example to create projects with brewery references. First version includes beer functions to get beers by page, filter, and id. Brewery functions gets all breweries same as beer: by page, filter, and id. The second version displays asynchronous beer service and synchronous guice module.

The project Brewery DB .NET SDK was created by ZenOfBeer to wrap the API and access data of regional breweries, beer style guide, and brewers guilds. Navigation includes source, commits, branches, and pull requests. Paul Christensen created this resource. Reach Paul@ZenOfBeer.com

The Brewery DB Node.js SDK by Brewery DB obtains the brewery data from Brewery DB. At this moment, the SDK only access data, it does not wraps the API completely. Use npm to install. Learn how to use this resource with the endpoints of beer, brewery, search, category, and style.
Simple Order PHP SDK by CyberSource allows developers to interact with the CyberSource Simple API, using PHP.
Simple Order Windows Perl SDK by CyberSource allows developers to interact with the CyberSource Simple API, using Perl.
Simple Order Linux Perl SDK by CyberSource allows developers to interact with the CyberSource Simple API, using Perl.
Simple Order .Net SDK by CyberSource allows developers to interact with the CyberSource Simple API, using .Net language.
Simple Order Java SDK by CyberSource allows developers to interact with the CyberSource Simple API, using Java.
Simple Order C# for Windows SDK by CyberSource allows developers to interact with the CyberSource Simple API, using C# language.
Simple Order C SDK by CyberSource allows developers to interact with the CyberSource Simple API, using C language.
TradeGecko Ruby SDK by TradeGecko provides developers a ruby interface to the TradeGecko API.
The E*TRADE VC++ SDK by E*TRADE allows developers to access E*TRADE's trading platform using Visual C++. This SDK includes libraries for handling authentication, accounts, market data, and orders.

The E*TRADE PHP SDK by E*TRADE allows developers to access the E*TRADE trading platform from their PHP applications. The SDK includes libraries for handling authentication, accounts, market data, and orders.

The E*TRADE Java SDK by E*TRADE allows developers to access the E*TRADE trading platform from their Java applications. The SDK provides code libraries for handling authentication, accounts, market data, and orders.

Related APIs: Skyscanner Live Pricing REST API v1.0
Description: The Skyscanner Python SDK by Skyscanner allows developers to integrate the Skyscanner API's Flights, Hotels, and Carhire methods into their Python applications. This SDK was tested with Python 2.7.

This is the iOS SDK for Olapic allowing developers to access and integrate the functionality of Olapic with iOS applications through Objective-C. Olapic is a crowdsourced visual content platform. Olapic offers eCommerce features for attracting customers, buying, and selling visual content and photos.

This is the iOS SDK for Sense360 that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of Sense360 with iOS applications and devices through Objective-C. Sense360 is a sensor intelligence platform that detects background, location, activity, and context around people using mobile applications.

This is the iOS SDK for Sense360 that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of Sense360 with iOS applications and devices through Swift. Sense360 is a sensor intelligence platform that detects background, location, activity, and context around people using mobile applications.

This is the Google Glass SDK for Nod that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of Nod with Google Glass applications and devices through Java. Nod develops products and tools for gesture and motion tracking.

This is the Android SDK for Nod that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of Nod with Android applications and devices through Java and C. Nod develops products and tools for gesture and motion tracking.

This is the iOS SDK for Nod that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of Nod with iOS applications and devices through Objective-C. Nod develops products and tools for gesture and motion tracking.

This is a Ruby SDK for BitReserve that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of BitReserve with other applications and devices through Ruby. Bitreserve is a digital currency platform for sending and receiving digital currency on top of Bitcoin.

This is a Python SDK for BitReserve that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of BitReserve with other applications and devices through Python. Bitreserve is a digital currency platform for sending and receiving digital currency on top of Bitcoin.
The BitReserve PHP SDK by Seegno allows developers to integrate the BitReserve API into their PHP applications. This SDK requires PHP 5.5+ with the cURL extension and the Guzzle library.

This is the Android SDK for SumUp that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of SumUp with Android applications and devices through Java and C. SumUp is a service that allows users to accept and process credit card payments via mobile devices with the SumUp application.

This is the iOS SDK for SumUp that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of SumUp with iOS applications and devices through Objective-C. SumUp is a service that allows users to accept and process credit card payments via mobile devices with the SumUp application.

This is the Android SDK for AppNexus that allows developers to access and integrate the functionality of AppNexus with iOS applications and devices through Java and C. AppNexus is an open and customizable advertising platform that specializes in real-time advertising.

The AppNexus iOS SDK by AppNexus allows developers to access and integrate the AppNexus API into their iOS applications built with Objective-C. This SDK was designed to work with the AppNexus Console and does not work with OAS.

Category: Personal Information Management, Classification, Notes, Office
Description: The Evernote OS X SDK by Evernote allows to interact with the personal information management features of the API. It aims to integrate personal & work organizational components into web applications for Apple devices. Resources of the SDK include Apple style docs, installation of Mac SDK & iOS SDK, and registration for an Api Key. Additional components explain how to make asynchronous calls to the API, installation prompts, and use the iOS app to create notes.

Category: Personal Information Management, Classification, Notes, Office
Description: The Evernote Windows SDK by Evernote allows to interact with personal information management features of the API. Windows users can benefit from the creation and usage of apps that could simplify life & work organization. Resources include setup with steps to register for an API Key or Token, include the library in the app, modify the startup code, and see the project in action.

Category: Personal Information Management, Classification, Notes, Office
Description: The Evernote Android SDK project by Evernote includes overview, prerequisites, download, demo app, usage SDK, and snippets. Now Android users could benefit from the creation and usage of the API personal information management features such as note taking, reminder listing, and life organizing. For more information about what the API can do for an integration strategy, visit http://dev.evernote.com/documentation/cloud/

Category: Personal Information Management, Classification, Notes, Office
Description: The Evernote iOS SDK by Evernote helps to interact with the API features of note taking, date remembering, and work organizing. This tool can be used with CocoaPods. Resources include a getting started guide with the Cloud SDK and a set up example with API key, developer token, framework, and test in action features.

The Intel® RealSense™ SDK by Intel integrates speech recognition, facial analysis, augmented reality, hand/finger tracking, and background segmentation. It aims to increase users' sensory experience with technologically modified 3D perceptions. Download the kit for free. Languages supported include C#, C++, Java, and JavaScript.

Tableau, the software company that aims to simplify data visualization, provides this Javascript SDK to integrate services into applications. This resource could be a fit for developers who are now working in business intelligence projects. Integration opportunities include analytics features into desktop applications and visualization features into cloud applications. The SDK can be used to display visualizations from Tableau Server, Tableau Public, and Tableau Online in web pages, dynamically load and resize visualizations, filter data, select marks in visualizations, respond to events in visualizations, export visualizations to an image or PDF file.

The Layer Android SDK provides access to the functionality of Layer for integration with Android applications and devices through Java. Layer is a communications tool for applications that allow application developers to offer chat, voice, messaging, and video options in their applications.

The Layer iOS SDK provides access to the functionality of Layer for integration with iOS applications and devices through Objective-C. Layer is a communications tool for applications that allow application developers to offer chat, voice, messaging, and video options in their applications.

Google AdWords Conversion Tracking and Remarketing iOS SDK by Google. With this resource, users can measure the effectiveness of Google AdWords campaigns in Apple apps. It also aims to monitor user engagement. Opportunities include integration in Mobile app installs, Mobile app Engagement, and Ads in mobile apps.

The Google AdWords Conversion Tracking and Remarketing Android SDK by Google affords to track the success of AdWords app promotions and allows to tag user activity in the app. Both functions serve to measure effectiveness and engage users at the same time.

Related APIs: Bing Translator REST API, Bing Translator RPC API
Description: The Bing Translator PHP Wrapper by Renjith is a library and PHP wrapper for the Microsoft and Bing Translator APIs. The Microsoft Translator services can be used in web or client applications to perform language translation operations.

Related APIs: Bing Translator REST API, Bing Translator RPC API
Description: The Bing Translator (FGTranslator) Objectice-C Library by George Polak is a tool for developers using the Bing Translator API. It is a simple iOS library for Bing translation APIs. The Microsoft Translator services can be used in web or client applications to perform language translation operations.

This is a Haskell SDK for developers interested in working with Textocat's API. Textocat offers text analysis tools, focusing mainly on Russian language news texts. This unofficial SDK is authored by Mansur Ziatdinov and is offered under an Apache 2.0 License.

This SDK is for JavaScript developers interested in working with the CloudBoost API. CloudBoost offers data-storage, realtime, search, graph, and geospatial database services. This official SDK supports the API's app building tools.

The SoundCloud PHP Library by Nelson J Morais offers the features of user authorization, user authentication, user credentials, flow authentication, access to GET, PUT, POST and DELETE references and download & upload media files. Requires PHP 5.3+

The SoundCloud Ruby SDK by SoundCloud offers methods to handle authorization and execute HTTP calls. Examples demonstrate how to print links of the 10 hottest tracks, work with OAuth2, initialize a client, and add a track to a playlist.

This Node.js SDK is for use with the Hacker News API. Use this SDK to retrieve the top 500 stories, the 500 newest stories, or Show, Ask, and Job stories on Hacker News. See the project page for code samples and full method descriptions. The node is offered under an MIT license.

Okta, the Identity as a Service company, provides a Python SDK with installation with pip; quickstart with client creation, user creation, user activation; and clients with auth, events, factors, sessions, and users. Additional notes to the documentation available on GitHub https://github.com/okta/oktasdk-python

Okta offers Identity as a Service with the aim to secure IT environments. As a resource, the API offers access to identity, authentication, and security features. As a supplementary tool, the Java SDK aims to simplify integration with desktop and mobile devices. Available in enterprise architecture, resources of this kit include guides to build, install, and run the build with tests.

Okta, an Identity as a Service company, offers its official Okta Power Shell SDK to access the API in CSharp. To work with this project, users can install Chocolatey and next install a PowerShell prompt. Resources include command list and troubleshooting. Okta API aims to facilitate the integration of identity and security into desktop and mobile applications. Create a free developer account to start https://www.okta.com/developer/signup/

Okta is about Identity as a service (IDaaS). The API provides REST functionalities that aim to facilitate identity creation, mobile management, and secure enterprise. In addition to the API, Okta offers an SDK in .NET language with guides to create a client, create a client against another environment, and create client with a proxy. It also offers CRUD operations, enumeration, and custom properties. See the example of Okta API in a music store https://github.com/okta/okta-music-store

Related APIs: John Deere Logistics REST API, John Deere MyJohnDeere REST API, John Deere Machine REST API
Description: The John Deere SDK by John Deere allows developers to integrate John Deere equipment data into their applications using the Equipment Interface Component (EIC). Developers can use this SDK to read and decode data generated by a John Deere display and to control machinery by creating guidance data, field boundaries, jobs, etc.
The Bitfinex Meteor SDK by Josh Rossi allows developers to integrate the Bitfinex API into applications developed with Meteor, a JavaScript framework.

Travelport is a company that focuses on e-commerce for travel purposes either by land or air. Users can benefit from this SDK that is available by request to create applications and increase sales. Technical requirements include Message Envelope SOAP 1.1, Message Transfer HTTP 1.1, Encryption SSL 3.0, and Web Service Description Language WSDL 1.1, an XML-based interface definition language. See more of what the SDK can do for a travel project at https://developer.travelport.com/euf/assets/developer-network/pdfs/desktop_SDK_factsheet.pdf

Related APIs: Alexa Web Information Service RPC API
Description: Obtain early access to the Amazon Echo SDK, that aims to engage customers with answers, music, and news. It works with recognition features based on the Amazon Web Services cloud. The potential of this kit is to build projects using the Alexa AppKit to enhance applications with speech processing functionalities. Sample code in Node.js is available at https://developer.amazon.com/public/solutions/alexa/alexa-skills-kit/docs/using-the-alexa-skills-kit-samples-node
The Google Analytics Node SDK by jsguy gives developers Google Analytics API access. This Node SDK's highlighted features are automated concurrency limiting and optional request caching.

The PredictionIO .NET SDK by Themos Piperakis interacts with the API capabilities of user behavior prediction; personalization of news, deals, and job openings; discovery of events, and match-making service. Resources include a quick start guide to generate sample data, generate recommendations, and generate sample rankings. For more info, contact developer themos@themos.gr

With the PredictionIO Android SDK, users can integrate prediction features into web and mobile applications. The API is about machine learning services for developers and data scientists who are interested in building prediction projects. According to the main site, developers like this service because is customizable and scalable, while data scientists prefer the service because it provides an interface for analysis and evaluation of parallel models. See more of the SDK at https://github.com/PredictionIO/PredictionIO-Java-SDK

This is the official Payeezy iOS SDK to integrate payments, credit cards, and e-commerce solutions into Apple Pay. A PDF guide in GitHub published by Atul, the same writer of the SDK, demonstrates how to install, create payment tokens, and integrate with Apple Pay. Guide available at https://github.com/payeezy/payeezy_ios/blob/master/guide/payeezy_iOS_SDK042015.pdf

The official Payeezy Android SDK aims to offer quick integration from FirstData into Android applications. Contains minimum technical requirements such as OS 4.0 (ice cream) and higher, an emulator, latest SDK version, a project to compile, latest version of Android studio, and Java JRE. It also recommends to have ready developer registration, API Key, and SDK download to get started with the project.

The Payeezy JavaScript library includes a number of steps to get started with integration along with a sandbox to test credit card, eCheck, and GiftCard features. This is the official JavaScript library. Payeezy invites developers to contribute and reach support@payeezy.com

Official BitReserve Ruby SDK. It contains personal access token, endpoints, OAuth and basic authentication, tickers, entities, cards, transactions, transparency, and invitation to contribute to the project. BitReserve is a company that specializes in secure and instant financial services at no cost.

BitReserve Python SDK by BitReserve. Includes getting started, authentication, an example to send a transaction, and additional resources. With this tool, developers will be able to build Python applications associated to bitcoin, banking, cryptocurrency, and currency services. For additional information, contact developer byrne@majordojo.com

With the BitReserve SDK, users can integrate PHP applications with the aim to simplify online currency services. Requirements include PHP 5.4.4 with CURL extension and Guzzle library. Includes guides to integrate with composer, create personal access token, get authenticated user, get user balances, get user cards, and create new transaction. Author Tiago Ribeiro invites developers to contribute. Contact tiago.ribeiro@gmail.com

The Keen.io iOS SDK was created to create analytics features into Apple applications. Overview includes installation and usage. In the usage section, developers can access information to add events, set global properties, use Geo location, upload to Keen, enrich data, and debug the app.

The official Java SDK allows to record Keen.io data from any Java application. Resources available on GitHub include an Android quick start with installation, gradle, maven, and JAR download. Some of the usage instructions explain how to build a keen client, use the KeenClient singleton, and work with the source.

Semantria, the sentiment and text analysis company based on cloud services, provides a JavaScript SDK with the aim to integrate API capabilities easier. API features include analysis from tweets, Facebook posts, reviews, and enterprise. Additional resources in different languages are available at https://semantria.com/support/developer/docs/sdks

Ziggeo API affords to integrate video recording and video playback with 2 lines of code. The purpose of the service is to create asynchronous material for the benefit of viewers. The Android Java SDK offers the possibility to integrate with Android devices. Resources explain how to integrate the video player and how to integrate the video recorder. Credits to libstream, an API that allows to stream with Android with few lines of code. Available https://github.com/fyhertz/libstreaming
Contact Dr. Oliver Friedmann, entrepreneur & computer scientist public@oliverfriedmann.com

Ziggeo is an asynchronous video service with recording and playback technology. The API offers to integrate with mobile and website applications using JavaScript language. In addition to the API, the iOS SDK has been designed with Apple devices in mind, providing documentation in GitHub with only 2 lines of code. Note that the Alpha stage is still in progress. Created by Dr. Oliver Friedmann and Gianlucca di Maggio.

Keen.io analyzes data to store in a cloud and detect patterns in the future. The API serves to write applications with data collection, data analysis, and data visualization. As an additional resource, the SDK in JavaScript offers interaction with the API, recommending to update any necessary versions. Tools in the GitHub JavaScript SDK page include how to create a project, get API keys, install the library, configure a new client, record events, querying, and visualizations. To request help, contact@keen.io

Semantria is a cloud-based service that focuses on sentiment analysis and text analysis. With the goal to make integration easier, Semantria offers a Java SDK for the RESTful API. This resource includes authentication, session manager, serializer, detailed analysis, and test application.

The Google Glass SDK allows to create personalized information with the goal to be perceived on Google Glass. The Google Mirror API is associated with this SDK that contains user interface, patterns, style, and glassware flow designer as the main resources available on the site. Google recommends 4 principles when designing for Glass: don't get in the way (of user experience), keep it relevant, avoid the unexpected, and build for people.

Vungle is a company that focuses on mobile advertising. It offers an engaging user experience with skippable and non-skippable ads, opt-in ads, and storefront ads. The SDK aims to turn applications into businesses. Available to download from the main site, along with support for Unity, AdobeAir, Corona, and Cocos2dx. Vungle offers a complementary guide that explains how to start monetizing in 10 minutes available at https://vungle.com/blog/2015/01/21/how-to-monetize-your-ios-app-in-10-minutes/
